message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with information theory and rate-distortion codes. Other likely sub-categories could include cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the paper deals with sequences and their reconstruction, cs.LG (machine learning) as rate-distortion codes are often used in compression and image processing, cs.CC (computational complexity) as the paper discusses the convergence of input-output statistics, and cs.DM (discrete mathematics) as the paper deals with discrete memoryless sources and channels.
